# Creatio Testing & Quality Assurance Rules

You have access to a comprehensive testing toolkit for Creatio instances. Use these tools to run health checks, validate data integrity, test API performance, simulate user workflows, perform load and security testing, and generate test reports.

## When to Use Testing Tools

ALWAYS use testing tools when the user asks about:
- Health check, system status, instance readiness
- Data integrity, orphaned records, referential consistency
- API performance, response times, latency benchmarks
- Configuration validation, settings review
- Regression testing, snapshot comparison
- User workflow simulation, end-to-end testing
- Load testing, stress testing, capacity planning
- Security testing, penetration testing, vulnerability scan
- Business process testing, process execution validation
- Test results, test history, trend analysis
- Performance diagnostics, bottleneck identification
- Capacity planning, scaling recommendations

## Tool Reference — SMB Tier (7 tools)

### Health & Validation

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
|---|---|
| Extended health check, system readiness, diagnostics | `creatio_health_check_extended` |
| Data integrity, orphans, referential consistency | `creatio_test_data_integrity` |
| API response times, endpoint latency | `creatio_test_api_performance` |
| Configuration correctness, settings validation | `creatio_test_configuration` |

**`creatio_health_check_extended`** — Goes beyond the basic `creatio_health_check` (from deployment tools). Measures login endpoint latency, OData query latency, compile endpoint availability, and ClioGate reachability. Returns a per-component health status (healthy/degraded/critical) with response times and recommendations.

**`creatio_test_data_integrity`** — Scans for orphaned lookups, duplicate records, null required fields, and date consistency issues. Accepts an optional `entityName` parameter to focus on a specific entity (auto-discovers custom entities if omitted), and an optional `checkType` parameter (`"orphans"`, `"duplicates"`, `"nulls"`, `"dates"`, or `"all"` — default: `"all"`).

**`creatio_test_api_performance`** — Sends concurrent OData read requests and measures min/max/avg/p95 response times, success rate, and throughput. Accepts optional parameters: `concurrency` (number of concurrent requests, default 10, max 50), `entity` (OData entity to query, default `"Contact"`), and `durationSeconds` (test duration, default 5, max 30).

**`creatio_test_configuration`** — Validates instance configuration: custom package count, custom schema count, package dependency graph, and ClioGate version compatibility. Reports issues found with severity levels.

### Regression & Simulation

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
|---|---|
| Capture/compare regression snapshots | `creatio_test_regression_snapshot` |
| Concurrent API load test, session stability | `creatio_test_user_simulation` |
| View past test results | `creatio_list_test_results` |

**`creatio_test_regression_snapshot`** — Captures a snapshot of entity counts, custom schema count, package list, and OData response time. Use `mode: "capture"` to save a baseline, `mode: "compare"` to detect changes since the last snapshot. Essential before and after deployments.

**`creatio_test_user_simulation`** — Concurrent API load test using the shared MCP session: sends N parallel request cycles (login → query Contact → read Account → logout) to measure instance stability under concurrent load. Not true multi-user isolation — all cycles share the MCP auth context. Accepts a required `userCount` parameter (number of concurrent request cycles, max 200).

**`creatio_list_test_results`** — Returns historical test results with timestamps, pass/fail status, and summary metrics. Accepts an optional `type` parameter to filter by test type (e.g. `"health"`, `"integrity"`, `"performance"`, `"load"`, `"regression"`).

### Basic Assessment Workflow

For a basic quality check, run the SMB tools in sequence:
```
creatio_health_check_extended → creatio_test_data_integrity → creatio_test_api_performance → creatio_test_configuration
```

Or use the guided prompt: **`creatio_run_health_assessment`** — runs all health and validation tools and compiles a unified report.

## Tool Reference — Enterprise Tier (8 tools)

### Load & Capacity Testing

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
|---|---|
| Advanced load testing, concurrent users, throughput | `creatio_test_load_advanced` |
| Capacity planning, scaling thresholds, growth projections | `creatio_test_capacity_planning` |

**`creatio_test_load_advanced`** — Full load/stress testing engine with ramp-up, spike, soak, and constant scenarios. Measures p50/p95/p99, error rates, throughput curves, and detects breaking points. Up to 5000 concurrent users. Accepts parameters:

| Parameter | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `maxUsers` | **Yes** | Maximum concurrent users (1–5000) |
| `scenario` | No | Load scenario: `"constant"` (default), `"ramp-up"`, `"spike"`, `"soak"` |
| `durationSeconds` | No | Test duration in seconds (default: 30, max 300) |
| `rampUpSeconds` | No | Ramp-up duration for `ramp-up` scenario |
| `targetEntity` | No | OData entity to target (default: `"Contact"`) |
| `environment` | No | Target environment name |

**`creatio_test_capacity_planning`** — Estimates instance capacity by running incremental load levels (10→50→100→200→500→1000 users). Returns estimated max concurrent users and scaling recommendations. Accepts an optional `targetEntity` parameter (OData entity, default `"Contact"`).

### Security & Process Testing

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
|---|---|
| Security testing, vulnerability scan, OWASP checks | `creatio_test_security` |
| Business process execution testing | `creatio_test_business_process` |
| Custom test scenarios with scripted steps | `creatio_test_custom_scenario` |

**`creatio_test_security`** — OWASP-aligned security checks: auth endpoint hardening, security headers, CSRF protection, cookie flags, rate limiting, and error info leakage. Returns a security score (0–100) and detailed findings.

**`creatio_test_business_process`** — Triggers a business process via ClioGate (or ProcessEngineService fallback), monitors completion via SysProcessLog, and reports timing and errors. Accepts parameters: `processName` (required), optional `testData` (JSON string with process input parameters), and optional `timeoutSeconds` (max wait for completion, default 60, max 300).

**`creatio_test_custom_scenario`** — Executes a user-defined test scenario: a JSON array of steps with endpoint, method, body, assertions (statusCode, maxResponseMs, bodyContains), and repeat count. Accepts a `scenario` parameter (JSON string of the steps array).

### Regression & Reporting

| When user asks about... | Use this tool |
|---|---|
| Full regression test suite across all entities | `creatio_test_regression_full` |
| Export test reports (JSON, Markdown, JUnit) | `creatio_test_report_export` |
| Trend analysis across historical test runs | `creatio_test_trend_analysis` |

**`creatio_test_regression_full`** — Comprehensive regression suite: API endpoint availability (OData, AuthService, ClioGate), CRUD on custom entities, and cross-entity referential integrity. Accepts an optional `baselineId` parameter (previous test result ID) to compare against and detect regressions.

**`creatio_test_report_export`** — Exports a test result in JSON, Markdown, or JUnit XML format for CI/CD integration. Accepts a required `testResultId` parameter (ID of the test result to export) and a required `format` parameter: `"json"`, `"markdown"`, or `"junit"`.

**`creatio_test_trend_analysis`** — Analyzes performance trends over multiple test runs: response time degradation, error rate increases, capacity changes. Accepts a required `type` parameter (test type to analyze, e.g. `"health"`, `"performance"`, `"load"`) and an optional `count` parameter (number of recent runs to analyze, default 10, max 50).

